1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 g6 3. c3 Bg7 4. d4 cxd4 5. cxd4 d5 6. exd5 Nf6 { The main idea is to recapture the pawn on d5 with a knight and play against the isolated pawn. } 7. Nc3 (7. Bb5+ Nbd7 8. Nc3 (8. d6 O-O 9. dxe7 Qxe7+ 10. Qe2 Re8) 8... O-O 9. O-O Nb6 10. Re1 Nbxd5 { Eventually Black regains the d5 pawn and it is a balanced isolated queen pawn position. }) 7... O-O 8. Bc4 Nbd7 9. Bb3 Nb6 10. O-O Nbxd5 11. Re1 b6 12. Bg5 Bb7 13. Ne5 Rc8 14. Rc1 { Balanced position. Minor piece trades are favorable for Black due to the isolated d-pawn } *


