1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 g6 3. Bc4 Bg7 4. O-O (4. c3 e6 5. d4 cxd4 6. cxd4 d5 7. exd5 exd5 8. Bb5+ Nc6 9. O-O Ne7 10. Nc3 O-O { Black has the better position because the d4 pawn is more vulnerable for White than d5 for Black because of the fianchetto. }) 4... Nc6 5. c3 e6 6. d4 cxd4 7. cxd4 d5 8. exd5 exd5 9. Re1+ Nge7 10. Bb5 O-O { Like the sub variation above, Black has the better position because the d4 pawn is more vulnerable for White than d5 for Black because of the fianchetto. } *


