1. e4 c5 2. d4 cxd4 3. c3 d3 { Accepting the gambit with dxc3 is fine for black, but requires a lot of theory and still Black has to be cautious. d3 forces White into a Maroczy Bind, which could be a psychological plus because smith Morra Gambit players are usually attacking players. Maroczy Bind is more positinoal in nature } 4. Bxd3 Nc6 5. c4 g6 6. Nc3 Bg7 7. Nf3 d6 8. h3 Nf6 9. O-O Nd7 { Sneaky threat of Bxc3, creating double isolated c-pawns for White. } 10. Be3 Bxc3!? 11. bxc3 Nc5 12. Bc2 Be6 { Black has to prove that the doubled c-pawns are a greater weakness for White than Black's weak dark squares on the kingside. } *


