1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 g6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nc6 5. Nc3 Bg7 6. Be3 Nf6 7. Bc4 O-O 8. f3? Qb6! { White has asked for too much, and now the dark squares in his territory is loose. b2 is being attacked, and Black is eyeing the d4 knight with tactics. } 9. Bb3 (9. Qd2? Nxe4 10. Nxc6 Nxd2 11. Nxe7+ Kh8 12. Bxb6 Nxc4 13. Bf2 Nxb2) 9... Nxe4 { This is a forcing sequence for White to not lose a pawn. Worth memorizing! } 10. Nd5 Qa5+ 11. c3 Nc5 12. Nxc6 dxc6 13. Nxe7+ Kh8 14. Nxc8 Raxc8 15. O-O Rcd8 { About equal here, but Black has a pleasant position. } *


