1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 g6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nc6 5. Nc3 Bg7 6. Be3 Nf6 7. Be2?! { Fairly passive move. The drawback is the important d5 square is not defended enough. } 7... O-O 8. O-O d5! { Striking in the center. } 9. exd5 Nb4 (9... Nxd5 { Also playable. } 10. Nxd5 Qxd5 11. Bf3 Qc4 { There will be a series of trades which lead to a drawn endgame. 9. Nb4 avoids dull trades. }) 10. Bf3 (10. d6 Qxd6) 10... Nbxd5 11. Nxd5 Nxd5 { Good position for Black } *


