1. e4 c5 2. Nc3 Nc6 3. g3 g6 4. Bg2 Bg7 5. d3 d6 6. Be3 e5 7. Nh3 { Setting up the Reversed Botvinnik structure bind } 7... Nge7 8. f4 Nd4 9. O-O O-O 10. Qd2 Bg4 11. Ng5 f6 12. Nf3 Qd7 13. Rf2 b5 14. Raf1 Rac8 15. Nd1 exf4 16. Bxf4 d5 { Striking back in the center, ultimately gaining space on all sides of the board. } 17. Nxd4 cxd4 18. Bh6 dxe4 19. dxe4 Nc6 20. Bxg7 Kxg7 21. c3 Rcd8 22. cxd4 Bxd1 23. e5 fxe5 24. d5 Bg4 25. Rxf8 Rxf8 26. Rxf8 Kxf8 27. Qf2+ Ke7 28. Qc5+ Qd6 29. Qc1 Nb4 30. Qg5+ Kf7 31. Qxg4 { White should have taken the knight and trade off into an equal bishop endgame. However, in this variation, the knight and queen dominates with the initiative. } 31... Qc5+ 32. Kf1 Qc1+ 33. Ke2 Qxb2+ 34. Ke3 Qc3+ 35. Ke2 Qb2+ 36. Ke3 Nc2+ 37. Kd2 Nd4+ 38. Ke3 Nf5+ 39. Kf3 { A nice queen sacrifice leads to a winning king and pawn endgame } 39... Qxg2+ { 0-1 White resigns. } 0-1


