1. e4 c5 2. Nc3 d6 3. g3 g6 4. Bg2 Bg7 5. d3 Nc6 6. Be3 e5 7. Qd2 Be6 8. Nge2 Nd4 9. O-O Ne7 10. Nd5 Nxd5 11. exd5 Bg4 12. Nxd4 cxd4 13. Bh6 O-O 14. Bxg7 Kxg7 15. c3 Qb6 16. Rae1 Qc5 17. cxd4 exd4 18. Re7 Rae8 19. Rfe1 Rxe7 20. Rxe7 Rc8 21. h3 { Turns out the c-file is the more important file to dominate } 21... Qc1+ 22. Qxc1 Rxc1+ 23. Kh2 Bf5 24. Rxb7 Bxd3 25. Rb4 Rc4 26. Rxc4 Bxc4 27. Kg1 { The passed d-pawn turns out to be a huge strength which contributes to Black's win } 27... d3 28. b3 (28. Kf1?? d2+) 28... d2 29. Bf3 Bxd5! 30. Bd1 Kf6 31. f4 Be6 32. h4 h5 33. Kf2 Bg4 { Basically forces the exxchange of bishops and into a winning king and pawn endgame. } 34. Bxg4 hxg4 35. Ke2 Kf5 36. Kxd2 Ke4 37. Ke2 d5 38. b4 Kd4 39. a4 Kc4 40. b5 Kb4 41. f5 Kxa4 (41... gxf5?? { Black cannot capture or else White gets a passed h-pawn } 42. h5) 42. Ke3 Kxb5 43. Kf4 a5 44. Kg5 a4 45. fxg6 fxg6 46. Kxg6 a3 47. h5 a2 48. h6 a1=Q 49. h7 Qh8 { 0-1 White resigns. } 0-1


