1. e4 c5 2. Nf3 g6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 d6 6. Be3 Bg7 7. f3 Nc6 8. Qd2 O-O 9. Bc4 Bd7 10. O-O-O Rb8 11. Bb3 Na5 12. Bh6 Bxh6 13. Qxh6 b5 14. g4 b4 15. Nd5 Nxb3+ 16. Nxb3 e5 17. Ne3 Be6 18. h4 Kh8 19. Qg5 (19. h5?? { White should not blindly further his attack. h5 leads to his Queen getting trapped } 19... Ng8) 19... Rb6 20. Na5 Kg7 21. Nf5+ Bxf5 22. gxf5 Qc7 23. fxg6 fxg6 24. h5 Rc8 { Best defense is a strong offense! } 25. Rd2 Ra6 26. hxg6 h5 { Acts as a distraction to take the initiative } (26... hxg6?? { Recapturing is just too dangerous because White seizes the important initiative with Rg2. Black cannot proceed on the queenside since checkmate looms on the kingside. Black is one move short. } 27. Rg2) 27. Nb3 (27. Rxh5 Nxh5 28. Qxh5 Rh8) 27... Rxa2 28. Kb1 Ra6 29. Qf5 Qc4 30. Re1 Rc5 31. Rf2 Rca5 32. Re3 (32. Nxa5 Rxa5 { Black enters on the a-file and things get messy. Notice how safe Black's king is thanks to the Nf6. } 33. b3 Qc3) 32... Qd4 33. Nxa5 Qd1+ 34. Ka2 Rxa5+ 35. Kb3 Qa1 36. c3 Qa4+ 37. Kc4 bxc3+ { 0-1 White resigns. } 0-1


